          "description": "I came in for continuation of rabies post-exposure vaccination (dose #3) with full documentation. The provider refused to administer the vaccine, incorrectly insisted I needed HRIG at this stage, and would not explain the medical reasoning.\n\nWhen I asked if the vaccine could be given here or if they could coordinate with another urgent care, the doctor ended the conversation and walked out (\u201cI\u2019m going to step out\u201d). No handoff, no explanation, no attempt to help.\n\nThis was unprofessional, dismissive, and extremely frustrating, especially given the anxiety around rabies exposure. If a clinic is unwilling or unable to manage standard follow-up care, patients should be told respectfully and clearly \u2014 not shut down.\n\nI would not return here for anything time-sensitive or complex.",
