          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUPFV-zvHpHNIE0w0gzVAS5koDBQpI-6opWGH8BD0Jb_WoiSWF9jA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "You can put lipstick on a pig, but it\u2019ll still be a pig sums up my experience at this CityMD.  I took a bad fall after arriving in NYC for a family vacation and was bleeding badly from my mouth. The hotel directed our family to this CityMD for urgent care. I was encouraged by the lack of a line and clean waiting area, but my experience went downhill from there. We had to do an online check in even though the guy at the front desk was doing nothing, which was long and cumbersome given I couldn\u2019t type as I was holding a bloody gauze over my mouth so my frazzled husband had to do it for me.  When we finally got into the exam room, I could barely understand the doctor (who had a thick accent), and the odd tension between him and the nurse was uncomfortable. He looked in my mouth and immediately told me I had to go to the ER. I didn\u2019t get aspirin, a tetanus shot, nothing. I felt like I must be on a candid camera show as the whole experience was such a joke.  The visit was less than five minutes, yet they billed my insurance $300. Also, at this point my family had left to get food (as it was several hours since we\u2019d eaten), so I was left in pain, crying, and trying to make my way to an NYC ER by myself and you cannot catch a cab or car service in front of this CityMD location because cars cannot drive in front of it! And, they had told me to go to the NYU ER, but when I put the address they had given me in the Lyft app the address was coming up as pediatric only. I went back into the CityMD office to clarify where I should go, and the new guy then at the front desk told me I should actually go to Mount Sinai ER (side note to CityMD - don\u2019t send patients to Mount Sinai - that\u2019s incredibly unkind as it\u2019s a madhouse there). I will say that front desk guy was the only person who showed a little bit of care at CityMD by taking pity on me and hailing me a cab; however, the address CityMD gives you for the Mount Sinai ER is actually not for the ER but for the main hospital, so I just found myself waiting again only to be told that I was in the wrong place.  Save yourself time and money - skip CityMD, and seek attention from competent medical professionals.",
